(165, 'Karen', 'Kazmer', NULL, 'Kazmer has shown mostly in Canada and western US. She is best known for public art projects,  installations and mixed media constructions. She is a part-time instructor at Emily Carr Institute of Art and Design, Vancouver.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=170', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ImageDisplay.aspx?AreaId=170&ImageId=532', 2),
(166, 'Wolfgang', 'Kubach', NULL, 'Kubach was born in 1936. He and Anna-Maria Kubach-Wilmsen worked as a team. They came to Vancouver in 1976 to do the piece for the Vancouver International Stone Sculpture Symposium.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=171', NULL, 5),
(167, 'David', 'MacWilliam', NULL, 'After receiving his BFA at NSCAD MacWilliam settled in Vancouver. He taught at SFU from 1980-87 and has taught at ECIAD since 1988. He is primarily a  painter and has a longstanding interest in abstraction.  His work is in collections at the VAG, the CC Art Bank, the AGGV and private collections.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=172', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ImageDisplay.aspx?AreaId=172&ImageId=533', 2),
