(545, 'Jay', 'Havens', 'http://www.jayhavens.me/', 'Jay Havens is a multidisciplinary artist of Haudenosaunee-Mohawk and Scottish-Canadian ancestry and member belonging to the Six Nations of the Grand River, Mohawk Bear Clan. He works accross Turtle Island as a freelance designer, artist in residence, and educator for production companies, post-secondary institutions and school districts alike. Havens is most interested in opportunities which inform audience ideas around Indigeneity. ', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=565', NULL, 2),
