(38, 'B.C. Centennial Fountain', 'Removed', '1966-01-01', 'Vancouver Art Gallery', '750 Hornby Street', 'The fountain was commissioned by the BC Government in 1966 when the building was still a courthouse. The tile floor of the pool looks like water rippling and there are faces carved into the stone that rises in the middle of the pool.', NULL, '49.282879', '-123.120461', 'Bronze, ceramic tile', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ImageDisplay.aspx?AreaId=43&ImageId=35', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtworkDetail.aspx?ArtworkId=43', 3, 6, 2),
