(47, 'Requiem for Yan', 'In Place', '1986-01-01', 'Queen Elizabeth Theatre', '650 Hamilton', 'This rectangular tower with many angles and corners is constructed of stainless steel and copper tubing.', 'The piece was made as part of City Shapes in 1985-86. The artwork is a tribute to the strength of the pioneers and to  the artist\'s father, Hon Yan Young, who came to Canada to work on the railroad and became a foreman, translator, and merchant. The piece is a reference to an oriental puzzle box.', '49.280206', '-123.112934', 'Stainless steel, copper', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ImageDisplay.aspx?AreaId=53&ImageId=43', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtworkDetail.aspx?ArtworkId=53', 3, 1, 1),
