(323, 'Marking High Tide and Waiting for Low Tide Pavillions', 'In Place', '1996-01-01', 'David Lam Park', NULL, 'There are two sculptural elements below the pump station and along the southern shore of David Lam Park (located in North False Creek between the Granville and Cambie bridges) : a circle of stones and a concrete ring resting on columns. Text is inscribed on the inside of the concrete ring.', NULL, '49.271847', '-123.124910', NULL, 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ImageDisplay.aspx?AreaId=371&ImageId=297', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtworkDetail.aspx?ArtworkId=371', 3, 4, 12),
