(613, 'Snapshots of History', 'In Place', '2010-01-01', NULL, '490 Columbia Street', 'Snapshots of History is a visual time machine. One panel depicts the Goon family. The other two panels of the mural feature a reproduction of a 1905 photo of a silk merchant in Chinatown and a rendering of a 1936 photo of men sitting outside a barber shop at Carrall and Pender. ', NULL, '49.280674', '-123.101902', 'Paint', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ImageDisplay.aspx?AreaId=712&ImageId=923', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtworkDetail.aspx?ArtworkId=712', 12, 4, 6),
